        "title": "feat: add Claude Fable 5 support",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `claude-fable-5` as a first-class Anthropic model with 1M context and 128K max output support.\n- Apply Fable request rules from Anthropic docs: adaptive thinking via `output_config.effort`, no disabled thinking, no assistant prefill, no unsupported sampling, and non-streaming fallback for refusal-safe handling.\n- Preserve provider-native reasoning safely across Anthropic/OpenRouter-compatible history, cache identity, and conversation rollback paths.\n- Update model parsing, docs, changelog, and regression coverage for Fable, Opus 4.8 streaming risk, terminal content filters, stop conditions, cache keys, and compatible providers.\n\n## Tests\n- `swiftformat --lint .`\n- `swift test --filter 'MinimalModernAPITests|AnthropicInterleavedDefaultsTests|CustomProviderRegistryTests|ModelParsingTests|GenerationTests'`\n- `env -u OPENAI_API_KEY swift test --no-parallel`\n- Manual closeout review over provider request shaping, model detection, stream/content-filter rollback, cache identity, and defaults after final autoreview wrapper runs hung idle twice with empty output.\n",
